[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Hey guys, so ComfyUI Image Edit 2511 natively supports transferring poses from one image to another, but sometimes it does not work. That\'s where Any Pose LoRAs come in handy. They can transfer some complicated poses perfectly without'

[00:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the need for control maps. So, let\'s see how to use Any Pose LoRAs with ComfyUI Image Edit 2511. Let\'s get started. The download link for the Any Pose LoRAs is available in the description. Open that'

[00:25] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'link and you will see a page like this. Here we can see some of the LoRA. If you scroll down, you can find a lot of information regarding the LoRA. One thing to note is that the Any Pose LoRA'

[00:37] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'is not just one LoRA. It is two LoRAs. I know it may be confusing at first. We need two LoRAs, which are base and helper. Both LoRAs should be set to 0.7 strength. Well, you can definitely play'

[00:51] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'with the LoRA strength to see which works best for you. For the LoRA, the developer recommends a prompt, so you should be using this prompt for Any Pose to work. In some cases, the background might'

[01:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'change. So, there is another set of words recommended by the developer for stopping the background from changing. But, I found a better way to make sure the background does not change, which I will show you later.'

[01:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Now, let\'s focus on downloading the LoRA. Scroll up and click on files and versions. Here, we can find both the base and helper LoRAs. Download both of them. Then put the'

[01:28] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'LoRAs inside the LoRAs folder of ComfyUI. Now, let\'s switch to ComfyUI. So, here I have already built a workflow. I will give you a basic overview of this workflow so you can start using it. The'

[01:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'download link for the workflow is available in the description. So, let\'s have a quick overview of the workflow. In here, we have the image loaders. In the first image loader, we will load the'

[01:53] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'image where we are going to change the pose. Then, in the second image loader, we will load the image from which we are going to copy the pose. So, in the first image loader, let\'s choose another image. Let\'s go to the pictures folder,'

[02:05] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'and then let\'s choose a photo. And in the second image loader, let\'s choose another photo containing a different pose. Let\'s choose this one. So, we are going to transfer the pose from the'

[02:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'second image to the first image. Also, we don\'t need the third image loader, so let\'s keep it in bypass mode. Then, we have the subgraph node of QN Image Edit 2511. After spending so much time with it, I have to say this subgraph node is'

[02:31] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'a really good node that will simplify complex workflows. In this node, first, we have the prompt box where I\'ve written the prompt recommended by the developer of the Any Pose LoRA. I also added an extra sentence to make sure her'

[02:44] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'clothes don\'t change. Then, under the prompt, you can see I have selected FP8 mixed of QN Image Edit 2511. Then, the clip, which is the same text encoder I used in my other QN Image Edit'

[02:56] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'videos. Then, for the VAE, it\'s just the same VAE used for QN Image models. As you can see, I am using the eight-steps LoRA with a strength of 1.0. You can also try the four-steps LoRA for'

[03:09] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'improving generation speed. Then, I have selected the Any Pose Base LoRA with a strength of 0.7. Then, we have the Any Pose Helper LoRA with a strength of 0.7. The shift value is just the same value I'

[03:22] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'used in my other QN Image Edit videos. For now, I am using a fixed seed, but you can also use a random seed if the generation does not work properly. The steps is eight, the CFG value is 1.0,'

[03:34] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the sampler is Euler, the scheduler is simple, and the denoise value is 1.0. There is also an option for setting the output resolution based on image two. So, if you want to, you can use it.'

[03:47] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'But remember, it does not use the exact resolution of image two. For further changes, just enter into the subgraph and make your own modifications. Here, you can see that I have added the'

